      <title>FooBar&#43;&#43;</title>
      <link>/project/foobar/foobarplusplus/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 May 2018 17:38:55 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>/project/foobar/foobarplusplus/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/LongwoodFooBar/SeniorSeminarProject&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;FooBar++&lt;/a&gt; is a project I worked on for my Senior Capstone in Computer Science at Longwood University. It is a web-based system for Computer Science 160 and 162 students to test their code for projects and for instructors to assign work. Students will be able to work in a safe, sandbox environment. This system is built around operation on an internal network. It is intended to be run on Linux- or UNIX-based machines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other members of my team were:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/BenjaminByrnes&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Ben Byrnes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Jonathangunter1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Jonathan Gunter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/LittleBoyTimmy&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Joseph Harp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/btreyl11&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Brandon Lewis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Heatherms27&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Heather Switzer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/tylerzamoracarden&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Tyler Zamora-Carden&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
